text: Phillip Stephen Busbridge (4 September 1920 – 11 December 1975) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). He also served in the Royal Australian Air Force during World War II. == Notes == == External links == * *Profile on Collingwood Forever Category:1920 births Category:1975 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players Category:Australian military personnel of World War II
